                        <summary>Seven opinions on the preservation of good health</summary>
                        <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                        <msItem n="2" xml:id="WMS_Arabic_444-part2-item1">
                           <author>
                              <persName xml:lang="eng">Anonymous</persName>
                           <note>Ullmann Medizin p. 188, Ḥaddād/Biesterfeld no. 77
                              (Shelf-mark: 510/815 Ṣr / 126 /109) 
                              ollowing M. Ullmann (Ullmann Medizin p. 188), F. Ḥaddād and
                              H.H. Biesterfeld suggest that the author of the work is Muḥammad
                              aṣ-Ṣanaubarī. However on the title page the author is
                              indicated as Aristotle and in the introduction as al-Būnī.</note>
                           </author>
                           
                           <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="" type="uniform">Fuṣūl nāfi`a</title>
                           <title xml:lang="ar" type="variant">فصول نافعة</title>
                           <title xml:lang="en" type="standard">Useful Chapters</title>
                           
                           <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                           
                           <incipit>
                              <locus>Fol. 9b.37</locus>
                              قال بعض ال‍حكما احرز ان
                              تجمع بين ال‍بيض وال‍سمك وانهما يورثان ال‍قولنج
                           </incipit>
                           
                           <explicit>
                              <locus>Fol. 10b. 17</locus>
                              ال‍صدقه وال‍ذكر وال‍دعا اول
                              ل‍نهار تمت ول‍له علي كل شي قدير وال‍حمد ل‍له رب ال‍عالمين </explicit>
                        </msItem>
                     </msContents>
